<br>
Hmmm, Freeport is their first city book. That should be very interesting based upon the way White Wolf writes source material. It's bound to make the whole online version of the game more intersting as well as now many people will have access to information to back up what they see in the game.<br>
<br>
&lt;drool&gt;<br>
<br>
I can't wait. <p><b><i>Gnmish Gearbinder</i></b><br>Gnomish Rogue of Bristlebane - Ring Warden -  <a href="http://pub73.ezboard.com/bsullonzektavern">Sullon Zek</a><br><img src="http://gnmish.homestead.com/files/gnmisig.jpg" boarder="0"><br><i>"Shut up, you mouth breathing bottle baby before I go back in time and give your father a condom" - Tweety - Lum the Mad</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulordmaxwell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LordMaxwell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 4:16:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=33.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Most differences are in both Star Wars and WoT, and I think it's things that Jonathan Tweet is still kicking himself for not including in the basic books. (Like increased defense with level, simple, elegant and it works.)<br>
<br>
